Among other important proposals contained fora second presidential term, the election by the National Assembly members of the National Commission for the Elections (CNE, according to its Portuguese initials), the document contains an important dispositive concerning the electoral discount, that is, the number of votes received by the winning presidential candidate that is subtracted from the total vote. Out of the 147 candidates, there were only two who received more than 500,000 votes, while President dos Santos’ total to take office for a second six years was 601,000. The 100,000 votes that he did not reach were then subtracted from the vote of the Management Platform for Social Democratic Convergence program, winning with just less than 400,000 (399,400). There is a need to engage in a publicibus debate on the electoral discount, because it amounted to a loss of 162,715 votes. In sum, there were 131 less parliamentary alternati e possibili-
ties to choose and 8 parties that lost all the parliamentary opportunities.
